OL,3,CMan jailed for taking 'silly' pictures
OL,4,Cduring court case over boy's death
OL,6,FHe admitted taking the photos and
OL,7,Fdistributing them by uploading them to
OL,8,Fsocial media.
OL,10,FJudge Bindloss said: "This is a
OL,11,Fsensitive and serious case. They were
OL,12,Fon trial for violent disorder in which
OL,13,Fa young man was killed."
OL,15,F"You knew taking photos was not
OL,16,Fpermitted, you knew your brother was
OL,17,Fon trial. You were reckless as to
OL,18,Fwhether this trial would be disrupted.
OL,19,FLiam in one of your photos was seen to
OL,20,Fbe posing for you. There are emojis
OL,21,Fand the caption 'Slim Jim'.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/11
