OL,3,CMan jailed for taking 'silly' pictures
OL,4,Cduring court case over boy's death
OL,6,F"It's not accepted there was any
OL,7,Fintention to intimidate or interfere.
OL,8,FHe's a habitual poster on social media
OL,9,Fand acted incredibly stupidly. He
OL,10,Foffers his apology for what he had
OL,11,Fdone. He deleted the post as soon as
OL,12,Fhe realised the severity of what he
OL,13,Fhad done.
OL,15,F"Belonging to a generation where
OL,16,Feveryday life is posted constantly on
OL,17,Fsocial media, he has not come to court
OL,18,Fwith the aim of disrupting proceedings
OL,19,For prejudice the trial.
