OL,6,FThey were also found guilty of
OL,7,Fwounding with intent to commit
OL,8,Fgrievous bodily harm in relation to a
OL,9,Fsecond victim, who suffered an injury
OL,10,Fto his back.
OL,12,FCarlos Neto admitted wounding Gordon
OL,13,Fbut claimed it was in self-defence.
OL,15,FHe and co-accused Lawson Natty, who
OL,16,Fsupplied Neto with the machete used in
OL,17,Fthe attack, were remanded in custody.
OL,18,FThey will be sentenced on 8 March.
